---
title: Creamy Tuna and Spinach Salad with Pickled Red Onion, Cucumber & Garlic Bread
description: Oh, the things we can do with a simple can of tuna! Exhibit A: This light-yet-satisfying dinner salad idea that’s on the table in just 20 minutes. This protein-rich bowl starts with a homemade lemon-mustard dressing tossed with tender baby spinach leaves and crunchy, refreshing cucumber slices. You’ll top it all with a dollop of creamy tuna salad featuring tangy pickled red onion (pretty in pink!) A side of buttery garlic bread adds a crisp and savory element, rounding out the meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/creamy-tuna-spinach-salad-c1af2135.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/creamy-tuna-spinach-salad-63fe39880bac84ba7f041011-c6a8d4bf.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 620 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 42 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1060 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-tuna-spinach-salad-63fe39880bac84ba7f041011
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Mediterranean
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees.

> TIP: If you have a toaster oven, feel free to skip preheating—you'll use it to toast the ciabatta in Step 4.

Place @butter{1%tsp}(softened) in a #small bowl{} to soften. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced). Halve @ciabatta bread{1}. Quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into half-moons.

In a #large microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave for ~{30-60%seconds}. Remove plastic wrap and set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Open @tuna{5.6%oz}(canned) and drain; place in a #medium bowl{}.

Stir in @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, and @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir a drizzle of @olive oil{5%tsp} and a pinch of @garlic powder{} into bowl with softened @butter{1%sachet}. Lightly season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Spread garlic butter onto cut sides of ciabatta; place on a #baking sheet{}.

> TIP: For easy cleanup, line baking sheet with aluminum foil first.

Toast on top rack until golden brown, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: You can use your toaster oven instead.

Slice garlic bread into four triangles each.

In a second #large bowl{}, whisk together juice from one lemon wedge, half the @dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/4%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use juice from two lemon wedges, all the mustard, 2 TBSP olive oil, and ½ tsp sugar.

Add @baby spinach{5%oz}, cucumber, and as much pickled onion as you like (draining first) to bowl with dressing; toss to combine.

Divide salad between bowls. Top with tuna and more pickled onion if desired. Serve with garlic bread and remaining lemon wedges on the side.